  "prompt": "Why does your head hurt after you cry?",
  "response": "Crying can cause a headache for several reasons:\n\n1. Dehydration\n- Crying involves losing fluids through tears\n- Dehydration can lead to headache and tension\n\n2. Emotional stress\n- Strong emotions trigger the release of stress hormones\n- These hormones can cause muscle tension and constrict blood vessels\n- Tension and constriction can result in a headache\n\n3. Physical tension\n- Crying often involves tensing facial and neck muscles\n- This muscle tension can cause strain and lead to a headache\n\n4. Sinus pressure\n- Crying can cause inflammation in the sinuses\n- Increased mucus production and congestion can create pressure and pain\n\n5. Hormonal changes\n- Emotional crying can cause hormonal fluctuations\n- These changes can contribute to headache development\n\n6. Intense emotional release\n- The physical act of crying can be physically and emotionally draining\n- This exhaustion can trigger a headache\n\nTo help prevent or alleviate a post-cry headache, try:\n- Drinking water to stay hydrated\n- Practicing relaxation techniques\n- Resting\n- Taking over-the-counter pain relief if needed",
